PTRANSFORMER(1)               General Commands Manual                PTRANSFORMER(1)

NAME
       ptransformer - Batch image format converter to JPEG

SYNOPSIS
       ptransformer [--port PORT] [--quality QUALITY] [--help]

DESCRIPTION
       PicTransformer is a web-based tool that converts images to JPEG format
       in batch. It features drag-and-drop upload, batch conversion, and
       automatic transparency handling.

OPTIONS
       --port PORT
              Set the server port (default: 5000)

       --quality QUALITY
              Set JPEG quality 1-100 (default: 95)

       --help
              Show this help message

USAGE
       Start the server:
              ./start.sh

       Open http://127.0.0.1:5000 in your browser

       Supported input formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, BMP, GIF, TIFF, WebP, TIF

FILES
       ~/Dev/Pictransformer/
              Default installation directory

       ~/Dev/Pictransformer/uploads/
              Temporary storage for uploaded images

       ~/Dev/Pictransformer/converted/
              Temporary storage for converted JPEG files

EXAMPLES
       Start with default settings:
              ./start.sh

       Start on custom port:
              python3 app.py --port 8080

